# Solution Output

This directory contains the generated output for the data solution.

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- A target SQL Server instance (or container) must be available
- Modern `sqlcmd` must be installed and available in the PATH
- PowerShell 7.5 or higher

### Quick Start

1. Run the container script to create a local SQL Server instance:

   ```powershell
   .\Databases\Deployment\Container.ps1
   ```

2. Run the deployment script to create all databases, tables, stored procedures, and register modules:

   ```powershell
   .\Databases\Deployment\Deployment.ps1
   ```

## Output Structure

```
Databases/
  Deployment/
    Container.ps1         - Container creation script
    Databases.sql         - Database creation script
    Deployment.ps1        - Main deployment script
    SampleData.sql        - Sample data for development/testing
    ControlFramework*.sql - Control Framework registration
  <database>/
    <schema>/
      Tables/             - DDL scripts for tables
      Stored Procedures/  - ETL stored procedures
      Views/              - View definitions
Documentation/
  Documentation.md        - Auto-generated documentation
Tests/
  <database>/             - Referential integrity tests
```

